place.name: RODDEN
place.gazetteerText: RODDEN, a parish in Frome district, Somerset; 1½mile E by S of Frome r. station. Post-town, Frome. Acres, 990. Real property, £1, 831. Pop., 234. Houses, 50. The property is divided among a few. The living is a p. curacy in the diocese of Bath and Wells. Value, £220. Patron, Mrs. E. Edgell. The church is good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
